    "html":  "\u003cdiv style=\"display:flex; align-items:flex-start; justify-content:space-between; flex-wrap:wrap; gap:12px; margin-bottom:24px;\"\u003e\n  \u003cdiv\u003e\n    \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:600; color:#60a5fa; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.8px; margin-bottom:6px;\"\u003eDaily Economic Briefing\u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003ch2 style=\"margin:0; font-size:20px; font-weight:700; color:#e2e8f0;\"\u003eFriday, 12 June 2026\u003c/h2\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"display:flex; gap:8px; flex-wrap:wrap;\"\u003e\n    \u003cspan style=\"background:rgba(52,211,153,0.12); border:1px solid rgba(52,211,153,0.25); color:#34d399; padding:4px 12px; border-radius:6px; font-size:11px; font-weight:600;\"\u003eMOVE 69.45 Stabilizing\u003c/span\u003e\n    \u003cspan style=\"background:rgba(52,211,153,0.12); border:1px solid rgba(52,211,153,0.25); color:#34d399; padding:4px 12px; border-radius:6px; font-size:11px; font-weight:600;\"\u003eSOFR 3.59% Easing\u003c/span\u003e\n    \u003cspan style=\"background:rgba(96,165,250,0.12); border:1px solid rgba(96,165,250,0.25); color:#60a5fa; padding:4px 12px; border-radius:6px; font-size:11px; font-weight:600;\"\u003eNFCI \u0026#8722;0.506 Loose\u003c/span\u003e\n    \u003cspan style=\"background:rgba(251,191,36,0.12); border:1px solid rgba(251,191,36,0.25); color:#fbbf24; padding:4px 12px; border-radius:6px; font-size:11px; font-weight:600;\"\u003eSENTIMENT 10:00 ET\u003c/span\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a1f2e; border:1px solid #2d3748; border-radius:12px; padding:20px; margin-bottom:20px;\"\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:600; color:#94a3b8; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.6px; margin-bottom:14px;\"\u003e\u0026#128202; Liquidity \u0026amp; Stress Metrics \u0026#8212; The \u0026quot;Gnosis\u0026quot; Pulse\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:12px; color:#64748b; line-height:1.6; margin-bottom:14px;\"\u003eCurrent regime: Loose \u0026amp; Volatile (the bullet-train transition). Term-premium volatility is cooling while funding and financial-conditions gauges remain expansionary.\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"overflow-x:auto;\"\u003e\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; font-size:13px;\"\u003e\u003cthead\u003e\u003ctr style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #2d3748;\"\u003e\u003cth style=\"text-align:left; padding:8px 12px; color:#64748b; font-weight:600; text-transform:uppercase; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.5px;\"\u003eMetric\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"text-align:right; padding:8px 12px; color:#64748b; font-weight:600; text-transform:uppercase; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.5px;\"\u003eValue\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"text-align:left; padding:8px 12px; color:#64748b; font-weight:600; text-transform:uppercase; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.5px;\"\u003eMarket Context\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"text-align:center; padding:8px 12px; color:#64748b; font-weight:600; text-transform:uppercase; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.5px;\"\u003eStatus\u003c/th\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/thead\u003e\u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #1e293b;\"\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#e2e8f0; font-weight:500;\"\u003eMOVE Index\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; text-align:right; color:#34d399; font-weight:700;\"\u003e69.45\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#94a3b8; text-align:left;\"\u003eTerm-premium volatility has fallen below the 70 threshold as desks digest this week\u0027s CPI/PPI sequence ahead of the June FOMC meeting.\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; text-align:center;\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"background:rgba(52,211,153,0.12); border:1px solid rgba(52,211,153,0.25); color:#34d399; padding:3px 10px; border-radius:6px; font-size:11px; font-weight:600;\"\u003eStabilizing\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #1e293b;\"\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#e2e8f0; font-weight:500;\"\u003eSOFR Rate\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; text-align:right; color:#34d399; font-weight:700;\"\u003e3.59%\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#94a3b8; text-align:left;\"\u003eThe secured funding rate ticked lower, pointing to orderly repo and wholesale funding conditions.\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; text-align:center;\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"background:rgba(52,211,153,0.12); border:1px solid rgba(52,211,153,0.25); color:#34d399; padding:3px 10px; border-radius:6px; font-size:11px; font-weight:600;\"\u003eEasing\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#e2e8f0; font-weight:500;\"\u003eNFCI\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; text-align:right; color:#60a5fa; font-weight:700;\"\u003e\u0026#8722;0.506\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#94a3b8; text-align:left;\"\u003eThe weekly benchmark remains deep in loose territory, keeping the systemic liquidity floor intact.\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; text-align:center;\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"background:rgba(96,165,250,0.12); border:1px solid rgba(96,165,250,0.25); color:#60a5fa; padding:3px 10px; border-radius:6px; font-size:11px; font-weight:600;\"\u003eLoose\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"margin-top:16px; padding:14px 16px; background:rgba(96,165,250,0.06); border-left:3px solid #60a5fa; border-radius:0 8px 8px 0;\"\u003e\n    \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:10px; font-weight:700; color:#60a5fa; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.6px; margin-bottom:6px;\"\u003eGnosis Interpretation\u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:13px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003eThe cross-metric signal confirms the \u0026quot;Bullet Train\u0026quot; thesis for today: MOVE has retreated to 69.45, SOFR is easing at 3.59%, and NFCI remains loose at \u0026#8722;0.506. That mix argues for capital being pushed out of volatile fixed income and back toward equities and risk assets. Intraday pullbacks remain mechanical unless funding conditions reverse.\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a1f2e; border:1px solid #2d3748; border-radius:12px; padding:20px; margin-bottom:20px;\"\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:600; color:#94a3b8; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.6px; margin-bottom:14px;\"\u003e\u0026#128197; Economic Calendar: 2026-06-12\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:12px; color:#64748b; line-height:1.6; margin-bottom:14px;\"\u003eConfirmed macro windows for today\u0027s session. University of Michigan confirms preliminary June sentiment at 10:00 ET; BLS confirms Employer Costs for Employee Compensation at 10:00 ET. The draft Import / Export Prices item was omitted because BLS schedules that May release for June 16.\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"overflow-x:auto;\"\u003e\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; font-size:13px;\"\u003e\u003cthead\u003e\u003ctr style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #2d3748;\"\u003e\u003cth style=\"text-align:left; padding:8px 12px; color:#64748b; font-weight:600; text-transform:uppercase; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.5px;\"\u003eEvent\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"text-align:center; padding:8px 12px; color:#64748b; font-weight:600; text-transform:uppercase; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.5px;\"\u003eEST (US)\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"text-align:center; padding:8px 12px; color:#64748b; font-weight:600; text-transform:uppercase; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.5px;\"\u003eGMT+8 (Local)\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"text-align:center; padding:8px 12px; color:#64748b; font-weight:600; text-transform:uppercase; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.5px;\"\u003eImportance\u003c/th\