yle=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#94a3b8; text-align:center;\"\u003e22:00\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; text-align:center;\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"color:#f87171; font-weight:600; font-size:12px;\"\u003eHigh\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#64748b; font-size:12px;\"\u003ePart of the Michigan preliminary release; desks will scan 1-year and 5-year inflation expectations for policy-path repricing.\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a1f2e; border:1px solid #2d3748; border-radius:12px; padding:20px; margin-bottom:20px;\"\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:600; color:#94a3b8; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.6px; margin-bottom:14px;\"\u003e\u0026#127963;\u0026#65039; Geopolitical \u0026amp; Fed Watch\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(96,165,250,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(96,165,250,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:14px 16px; margin-bottom:12px;\"\u003e\u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:700; color:#60a5fa; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.5px; margin-bottom:10px;\"\u003eMajor Macro Horizons (FOMC Blackout)\u003c/div\u003e\u003cul style=\"margin:0; padding-left:18px; font-size:13px;\"\u003e\u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:8px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe Strategic Pause:\u003c/strong\u003e The Fed is inside the June 6-18 blackout window before the June 16-17 FOMC meeting, so official reaction functions are silent while markets process spot data.\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:8px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe Easing Shadow:\u003c/strong\u003e Rate options remain focused on whether cooling bond volatility and loose funding can keep a structural pivot alive despite this week\u0027s inflation data.\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(239,68,68,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(239,68,68,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:14px 16px; margin-bottom:12px;\"\u003e\u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:700; color:#f87171; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.5px; margin-bottom:10px;\"\u003eTrump \u0026amp; The Iran Situation\u003c/div\u003e\u003cul style=\"margin:0; padding-left:18px; font-size:13px;\"\u003e\u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:8px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe Diplomatic Anchor:\u003c/strong\u003e The draft narrative frames Omani and Pakistani channels as stabilizing ceasefire structures. Treat the diplomatic timeline as narrative unless confirmed in live news flow.\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:8px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCommodity Deflation:\u003c/strong\u003e The market message remains focused on whether oil risk premium stays contained; any renewed energy shock would transmit immediately into rates and inflation expectations.\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(251,191,36,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(251,191,36,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:14px 16px; margin-bottom:12px;\"\u003e\u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:700; color:#fbbf24; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.5px; margin-bottom:10px;\"\u003eFed Chair Kevin Warsh Watch\u003c/div\u003e\u003cul style=\"margin:0; padding-left:18px; font-size:13px;\"\u003e\u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:8px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAI Productivity Shield:\u003c/strong\u003e The draft framework keeps AI infrastructure investment as the disinflationary offset that lets the economy absorb inflation pulses without an old-cycle tightening reflex.\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:8px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCommunication Restructuring:\u003c/strong\u003e With the blackout in force, expectations for next week\u0027s Fed communication style become more important than speeches. Watch whether SEP visibility or governor commentary gets deemphasized.\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a1f2e; border:1px solid #2d3748; border-radius:12px; padding:20px; margin-bottom:20px;\"\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:600; color:#94a3b8; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.6px; margin-bottom:14px;\"\u003e\u0026#128200; Trading Strategy Note (ES Futures)\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(52,211,153,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(52,211,153,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:12px 16px; margin-bottom:10px; font-size:13px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe Breakout Matrix:\u003c/strong\u003e The late-April swing-high break and May 1 expansion candle remain the macro baseline. Localized volatility is option-market shakeout unless it breaks the daily bull structure.\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(96,165,250,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(96,165,250,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:12px 16px; margin-bottom:10px; font-size:13px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTarget Levels:\u003c/strong\u003e Structural targets remain locked on the year-end Wall Street High Call zone of 8,447 to 8,477 on S\u0026amp;P 500 futures.\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(251,191,36,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(251,191,36,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:12px 16px; margin-bottom:10px; font-size:13px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eOrder-Flow Execution:\u003c/strong\u003e During the 10:00 ET University of Michigan window, monitor 1.5k volume charts in MotiveWave for sentiment-driven stop-hunts. Do not fade all-time-high expansion; manage VAL flushes as structural buy candidates only when absorption confirms.\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(148,163,184,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(148,163,184,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:12px 16px; margin-bottom:10px; font-size:13px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe Williams Rule:\u003c/strong\u003e Keep position size disciplined into the June 16 natural-cycle date. The setup remains expansionary, but the final approach to FOMC can keep the intraday path sharp.\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e"
